changeMaxMintAllowed(uint256).details: You can add requirements to prevent the _maxMintAllowed from being too low or too high

constructor.details: The recommended format is as follows: "ipsf//:{your CID}"

params._newBaseURI: indicate the URI of your NFT series

params._to: address where you want to send the nft gift

params._amount: is the number of NFT you want to mint

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.index: an index of the payee array

release(address).details: Triggers a transfer to `account` of the amount of Ether they are owed, according to their percentage of the total shares and their previous withdrawals.

release(address,address).details: Triggers a transfer to `account` of the amount of `token` tokens they are owed, according to their percentage of the total shares and their previous withdrawals. `token` must be the address of an IERC20 contract. This function is onlyTeams.

returns._0: amount of Ether already released to a payee

released(address,address).details: `token` should be the address of an IERC20 contract.

returns._0: amount of `token` tokens already released to a payee

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

total amount of Ether already released

totalReleased(address).details: Getter for the total amount of `token` already released. `token` should be the address of an IERC20 contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
